ElementDescription: "When child is doing things with you or talking with you, how often does he/she look in the eyes?"
If you call child's name, how often does he/she respond by looking at you?
If someone says "where's daddy (dad)?" or "where's mommy (mom)?" how often does child look at the correct person?
How often does child come get you just because he/she wants you to play with him/her?
"Does child ever use your hand like a tool to make it do something, such as putting your hand over a door handle or bottle top, in order to get it open? How often?"
"How often does child tell you about something that happened to him/her, such as if he/she fell down at the playground?"
"How often does child us his/her language for social purposes, such as chatting or making comments just to be friendly? "
"How often do you have to keep a conversation going with child, such as by continuously asking him/her questions? "
"When you ask child a Questions, how often does he/she respond to what you asked? "
"If you make a comment to child without asking a direct Questions, how often does he/she respond to what you said? "
Does child talk about the same topic to an unusual degree? How often does this happen?
How often does child start a conversation with you?
How often does child as you Questionss about your interest or experiences?
How often does child say things that others think are unusual or strange?
Some children use words or phrases that seem overly formal can sound like a "little adult" or "a little professor". How often does child sound overly formal?

Some children sound robotic or too flat when they talk. Others sound different because their voice is consistently too high pitched or sing-song like. How often does child sound different than other kids his/her age?

Some children have their own way of saying something that they say in the same way every time. For example, a child might say "3,2,1, blast off!" to mean they want to go outside, or "what can I do for you?" whenever they meet a new person.
How often does child verbally express an interest in having a play date with another child?
"When child see something interesting, how often does he/she hold it up or bring it over just to show you? "
"Some children point to request things. Others also point to show something of interest. How often does child use his/her finger to point out something of interest, such as pointing to an airplane?"
"Now I am interested in hearing about other gestures besides pointing. How often does child use simple gestures, such as waving good-bye or blowing a kiss, without being told to do so?"
How often does he/she nod his/her head to mean yes without being told to do so?
What if you are pointing something out to child? How often does he/she respond by looking at what you are pointing at?
How often does child smile at people?
"If child is not smiling already and you smile at him/her, how often does he/she smile back at you? "

"Some children show facial expressions that do not match the situation, such as laughing when it is not clear what is funny. How often does child show facial expressions that do not match the situation?"
Do child's facial expressions appear less natural compared to other children his/her age? For example, do his/her smiles ever look overly-practiced or rehearsed? How often?
Examples of Child's favorite things
"When child is excited about something, how often does he/she seem to want to get you to be excited, too?"
"How often does child offer to share food or other things with people, without being asked or told to share?"
"When someone else is hurt or sick, how often does child notice that something is wrong? "
When an adult outside of the family talks to him/her, how often does he/she respond appropriately, such as by smiling or saying "Hi!"?
"On the other hand, does child ever respond inappropriately to an adult outside of the family, such as by ignoring the person or turning away? How often does this happen?"
"In social situations, such as when eating at a restaurant, going to the grocery store, or attending a birthday party, how often does child show behaviors that are NOT appropriate to that situation?"
Does child prefer to spend time by him/herself? How often?
"When child is around other children his/her age, how often does he/she approach them or try to join in? "
"How often does child show interest in other children, such as by watching them or pointing them out to you?"
"If another child tries to interact with child, how often does he/she respond positively and do something to try to keep the interaction going? "
"When group of children are playing games such as hide and seek or duck-duck-goose, how often does child join in on his/her own and play?"

"When there are other children around, such as at a birthday party or during free time at school or daycare, how often does child stay on the edge of the group instead of interacting with the other children?"
"How often does child play pretend games with other children, such as playing house or school?"
"How does child make up his/her own stories using action figures or small dolls, such as pretending that the figures are going somewhere or doing something? "

Some children have very particular or ritualized ways of playing. They do not like to change from "their way" of playing with something and might get upset if others try to get them to play in a different way. How often does child insist on playing in a very particular way?

Some children who play pretend spend an unusual amount of time playing in certain ways, such as spending a lot of time pretending to be one character or pretending to have imaginary friends. Does child spend an unusual amount of time playing this way? How often?
How often does child disregard common "social rules?" This could include things like standing too close to people, interrupting, or asking overly personal questions.
How often does child seem socially awkward?
Does child refer to classmates or other people he/she knows as "friends" when they may not really be friends? How often?
How often does child have difficulty maintaining friendships or keeping after he/she makes them?
"During free time, how often does child seem to get stuck on doing the same activity for a long period of time. "

Some children seem more interested in playing with the parts of an object instead of using the whole object as it was intended. For example, when playing with a toy car, they might turn it over and spin the wheels rather than using it as a car. How often does child focus his/her attention on specific parts of toys or objects rather than using them as they were intended?
"Some children are overly sensitive to loud noises or are upset by certain sounds, sights, tastes, or feels of things. Is child bothered by any of these things? How often?"

"On the other hand, some children have sensory interest and like to seek out certain sensations. This might include looking at things in unusual ways, sniffing objects, or repeatedly touching certain textures. How often does child show sensory interests?"

"On the other hand, some children have sensory interest and like to seek out certain sensations. This might include looking at things in unusual ways, sniffing objects, or repeatedly touching certain textures. How often does child show sensory interests?"
Please Specify: ADIS_Preoccup
How often does child do/say things related to this unusual interest?
"Does child have any overly intense interest, such as in trains or geography or other special interests that take up an unusually large amount of his /her time? "
Please Specify: ADIS_CircumInt
How often does child spend time talking about/doing things related to this intense interest?
"Some children show repetitive hand movements, such as flickering their fingers or flapping their hands. How often does child move his/her fingers in these ways?"
"Some children show unusual repetitive whole body movements, such as hopping while waving their arms. How often does child move his/her body in these ways?"

Some children are bothered by minor changes in their daily routine. For example, a child might become upset if a different route to school is taken or if lunch happens 30 minutes earlier than usual. How often does child react negatively to changes like this in his/her day?

Some children need to do things in a very particular way or sequence. For example, a child might insist on touching the mailbox before going into the house or insist on closing doors that are open. How often does child insist on doing things in a very particular way or order?
